AWS Opswork

- Chef & Puppet help you perform server configuration automatically or repetitive actions
- They work great with EC2 & On-Premises VM
- AWS OpsWork = Managed Chef and Puppet
- It's an alternative to AWS SSM
- No hands on here, n knowledge of Chef and Puppet is needed
- In the exam: Chef & Puppet => AWS OpsWorks
- They help with managing configration as code
- Helps in having consistent deployments
- Works with Linux/Windows
- Can automate user accounts, cron, ntp, packages, services
- They leverage Recipes or Manifests
- Chef/Puppet have similarities with SSM/Beanstalk/CloudFormation but they're open source tools that work cross-cloud
